If Walmart shifted all wage increases onto the shoulders of consumers, every trip through the store would cost them 46 cents more.
They will spend in a year only $12.39 more than they do now.
Walmart supporters note with satisfaction that the protests took place in just nine states and did no harm to the group.
&quot;Black Friday&quot; continued in stores from 8 p.m. to midnight the next day, and Walmart sold 5,000 items per second during that period.
Its cash registers carried out a total of 100 million transactions for &quot;Black Friday&quot;.
