If on Mars the conditions are more suitable for life, the temperature on the surface of Venus is 500 .
You can only live there at very high altitudes or in the orbit of Venus...in space.
We began to take an interest in questions of reproduction in space, focusing on the flora.
Half a century ago, experiments were carried out on plants.
Four generations of orbit-grown peas were in no way different from earth varieties.
Then we put insects into orbit, small reproductive Drosophila flies.
In 1979, quail eggs were sent into space to see how an embryo developed in weightlessness.
We get a completely normal chick at the exit.
Then the problems start.
&quot;The problem is that the chick needs to find support, it needs to get on its feet and start moving,&quot; says the director of the laboratory of the Institute of Medico-Biological Problems of the Russian Academy of Sciences (IMBP) Vladimir Sychev.
Finding no support, the chicks fidgeted haphazardly.
And after 10 hours, newborns saw their instincts completely atrophy.
The chicks did not react to light or sound.
Unfortunately, they would simply die after four days.
&quot;We stared at them twice, then gave up, because it&#39;s just impossible to work with them there,&quot; says Vladimir Sychev, noting the failure of the experiment with the chicks in space. .
The last biological &quot;miniature ark&quot; with animals was sent into orbit 16 years ago.
The experiments will continue in the spring of 2013.
However, the &quot;Bion&quot; biosatellite will only carry species of the same sex.
There was an experiment with rats sent with their fetuses into space.
In principle, nothing supernatural has been discovered.
&quot;It was still about biosatellites and then it&#39;s the only experience. This kind of research must be carried out&quot;, points out Vladimir Sychev.
After landing, the space rats gave birth to their offspring.
Nevertheless, it is not yet possible to make reproductions directly in space.
This is not an easy task.
By losing their usual environment, animals are no longer able to realize their sexual instinct.
Unlike beasts, man is capable of this, in principle.
Homo sapiens possesses abstract thinking, he is able to create a suitable emotional background.
This type of experiment is not carried out for ethical reasons.
But women have been going into space for 50 years already.
The biggest risk was taken by Tereshkova.
And the female organism is what humanity has most precious.
