It has, for example, been said about me that I bribe journalists or that I was Jiří Paroubek&#39;s adviser.
Let&#39;s come to your visions.
You started the fight for the Castle with the themes of the material and criminal liability of politicians and retroactive tax declarations over twenty million [CZK] as your main concern.
To do this you must change the law.
As president, you have no such power and only the Senate as a whole can propose laws.
How do you want to solve this problem?
When, as a citizen, I pushed for the activities of tourist guide to constitute a liberal profession, I won my case.
The problem is politics: when someone arrives from the left or the right with a good project, it is knowingly refused and that delays the citizens.
As an independent, a member of no party, I have a much better chance of obtaining the support of all parliamentary parties.
I have the advantage of being able, without categorization and partisan dogma, to take from each party what is best for our country and implement it.
Do you consider yourself more of a right-winger or a left-winger?
From a Czech point of view, I feel like people put me on the left.
For me, whether it&#39;s a little left or right, it doesn&#39;t really matter.
For me, the important thing is that we move forward.
What matters to me is not whether people are left or right, but bringing people together.
I always support any solution contributing to the common good, even if it is proposed by the Communist Party or ODS and I act just as impartially against bad ideas.
Do you get mad when someone calls you a populist?
But doesn&#39;t what you said prove it?
When you make a business plan in a business, you also have a certain optimal goal and vision.
You try to get closer.
Some may call it populism, but all the proposals I&#39;m talking about have been applied by the world and recognized experts have spoken about them.
But without the support of parliament, you are left with only slogans.
You won&#39;t survive long in politics with that.
Do you think that if you go to see people and talk to them, you will succeed, for example, in imposing material and criminal liability?
I have no other option.
I have to convince politicians, journalists and public opinion and try to rally them to my camp in order to impose it.
If I were elected president, it would not be a problem to broadcast live on television my request to the presidents of the parliamentary parties to legislate on the material and penal responsibility of politicians, civil servants, judges and prosecutors.
