When there is a strong personality who will identify the abuses, it will be possible to put pressure on the political scene.
Take for example the election of the president by direct suffrage, it was obtained thanks to the pressure of public opinion.
I admit, bluntly, to being an amateur, and not a genius or an intellectual.
I try to find allies for my opinions and my visions.
I have just entered politics and I am trying to obtain the support of the majority for my program.
I try, on my own, to get things done, and if that doesn&#39;t work, I&#39;ll quit in six years and go back to the private sector.
It&#39;s a bit like Okamura had to save the Czech Republic.
