Since the early 1970s, Norway has owed its wealth to its oil and gas industry, one of the largest in the world.
&quot;But oil is not the only reason for our success,&quot; explains Anna, our waitress, with blonde hair and piercing blue eyes, the image of Nordic well-being, with a tray of rakfisk by hand.
We are - how do you say - careful people.
His English, like that of most people who live here, is perfect.
We are discreet, we do not like to be noticed.
Norway has managed its oil wealth very carefully - everything except a small percentage of money from this industry is invested in a special fund for the benefit of future generations.
