They hit each other, don&#39;t they?&quot;
I felt like homosexuals before the liberal legislation of the sixties.
Could I have just led a normal life in Oxford?
Would I have been forced to meet like-minded people only after dark?
Should I have become Labor and deny my opinions?
The next three years would be like a purgatory of ostracism and isolation.
The only openly Tory professor was Norman Stone, professor of modern history, who taught at my university.
He was hated not only because he was a Tory, but also because he was Thatcher&#39;s foreign policy adviser and one of the writers of her speeches.
He was almost never there.
He hated this provincial and insignificant place, as well as its adherence to the Marxist-determinist view of history.
In 1997, he accepted a professorship at Bilkent University, Ankara, Turkey.
