Yes, I would if I was angry or pissed off.
&quot;Even though I know it&#39;s cyberbullying,&quot; he says.
Key questions
Marielos Porras, English teacher and graduate in Education and Learning, considers that, to guide children and adolescents, we must understand that the purpose of social networks is to inform.
&quot;The Internet has emerged as a means of seeking information, but with the appearance of these sites, the rules of the game have changed&quot;, she mentions.
