Each week, students explore apocalyptic themes like nuclear war, zombies, viruses and germs, and global warming.
This semester, when religion professor Stuart Charmé decided to give a course on the end of the world, he knew he was throwing an irresistible hook: the end of the &quot;great countdown&quot; of the Mayan calendar, on December 21, to which refer many people as proof of the imminent end of the world.
